Release 1.0.21 - 2013-10-15

TypeChangesBy

Updated to latest version of ebeye-adapter, which fixes domain name (used to be chembl-compound, now is chembl-molecule). Fixes 182.rafalcan

Caught exceptions when there are any problems with the two main searches sent to EB-Eye, so that we can recover some results.rafalcan

Release 1.0.20 - 2013-09-26

TypeChangesBy

Updated to latest versions of uniprot-adapter, ebeye-adapter - which fixes issue with searches of disease names -, ep-util, rhea-adapter and rhea-ws-client.rafalcan

Deprecated use of config.xml from ep-domain to read EB-Eye domains (now using the Domains enumeration in ebeye-adapter).rafalcan

Removed a lot of rubish (unused methods, old commented-out code, excess blank lines).rafalcan

Better management of searches by using the proper queries (with/without enzyme filter, general or field-specific).rafalcan

Release 1.0.19 - 2013-07-26

TypeChangesBy

No longer contruct Compounds from a Map of String (names) rather now returns a collection of compounds from the mega mapper.joseph

Release 1.0.18 - 2013-06-19

TypeChangesBy

Fixed handling of accessions retrieved from the EBI search web service (now only the primary accession is kept).rafalcan

Updated to latest versions of ebeye-adapter and ep-util.rafalcan

searches various resources (OMIM,EFO,MESH) for Diseases using uniprot ID and returns the appropriate/related diseases to an enzyme or search termjoseph

Release 1.0.17 - 2013-06-11

TypeChangesBy

Updated to latest version of biobabel-core which implements proper sorting of compound names. Fixes 170.rafalcan

Fixed issue with leaking connections: the EnzymeFinder constructor created silently a connection to the mega-map, which was properly returned by this class but not by the subclass EnzymeRetriever. Now an existing connection is reused.rafalcan

Updated to latest version of uniprot-adapter.rafalcan

Release 1.0.16 - 2013-06-06

TypeChangesBy

All compounds for the small molecules tab (EnzymeRetriever) are now retrieved from the mega-map - the latest version of mega-mapper imports compounds more accurately -, instead of relying on different resources (used to be: mega-map for ChEMBL, IntEnz web service for cofactors, UniProt web service for drugs, activators and inhibitors). This is much faster, reliable and consistent.rafalcan

Added maximum number of compounds to retrieve to the search configuration.rafalcan

Updated to latest versions of ep-domain - with critic changes for small molecules -, chebi-adapter, literature-adapter, ep-util and uniprot-adapter.rafalcan

Avoided NPE when there are no citations. Fixes 162.rafalcan

Compounds are now retrieved for all of the orthologs in a summary, not only for the default one.rafalcan

Release 1.0.15 -

No changes in this release.

Release 1.0.14 -

No changes in this release.

Release 1.0.13 - 2013-04-05

TypeChangesBy

Processed PDB IDs for every related species in the summary (StructuresProcessor). Now the processing is not done after getting all of the summaries, and not only for the default species, but delegated to uniprot-adapter which can do it in paralel for every ortholog. The class StructuresProcessor is now deprecated. Fixes 146.rafalcan

Updated to latest version of uniprot-adapter - which allows fixing of PDB xrefs using the mega-map - and mega-mapper.rafalcan

Release 1.0.12

No changes in this release.

Release 1.0.11 - 2013-02-25

TypeChangesBy

Fixed 'connection already closed' issue caused by the Connection.close() method being called twice: one actively, then lazily from finalize(). Fixes 145.rafalcan

Updated to latest version of biomart-adapter.rafalcan

Release 1.0.10 - 2013-02-05

TypeChangesBy

Updated to latest version of parent pom file (move to GitHub), das-adapter, literature-adapter - which is faster retrieving citations from PDB -, mega-mapper - which fixes issue with querying by UniProt ID prefix - and junit.rafalcan

Added utility classes to process enzyme summaries. One of them - StructuresProcessor - replaces the list of PDBe identifiers coming from UniProt web services (including theoretical models) with the one coming from our mega-map (excluding them). Fixes 83.rafalcan

Release 1.0.9 - 2012-10-25

No changes in this release.

Release 1.0.8 - 2012-10-17

TypeChangesBy

Removed line which killed tomcat. Fixes 110.rafalcan

Removed duplicate declaration of intenzAdapter field, which was hiding the superclass'.rafalcan

Updated to latest versions of intenz-adapter - which can be configured now with a URL to retrieve IntEnzXML, namely web services -, literature-adapter - with faster searches -, reactome-adapter and mega-mapper.rafalcan

Release 1.0.7 - 2012-08-24

TypeChangesBy

Updated to latest version of intenz-adapter, which provides cofactors.rafalcan

Added cofactors to the model. Fixes 34.rafalcan

Release 1.0.6 - 2012-08-21

TypeChangesBy

Pathways related to a Rhea reaction are not redundant any more. Fixes 105.rafalcan

Release 1.0.5 - 2012-08-20

TypeChangesBy

Removed System.out.println's from the code. Using a proper Logger not to clutter catalina.out.rafalcan

Updated to latest versions of biomart-adapter, chebi-adapter and ep-util, which also get rid of System.out.println's.rafalcan

Updated to latest versions of intenz-adapter, ep-domain, ebeye-adapter, biobabel-lucene and junit.rafalcan

Release 1.0.4 - 2012-08-15

TypeChangesBy

Fixed query to Rhea web services (retrieving reactions by UniProt accession now, instead of EC number). Fixes 104.rafalcan

Updated to latest versions of rhea-adapter, biomart-adapter, uniprot-adapter, intenz-adapter, ebeye-adapter, reactome-adapter, das-adapter, chebi-adapter, literature-adapter, mega-mapper, ep-domain, rhea-domain, xchars and log4j.rafalcan

Release 1.0.2 - 2012-08-07

TypeChangesBy

Updated to latest version of parent, rhea-adapter, intenz-adapter, ebeye-adapter, ep-domain (removed duplicate dependency declaration, btw), ep-util, rhea-domain, xchars and log4j.rafalcan
